@adambom, I think it is an interesting idea, but I can imagine a case where you would want to do this on a per task basis as opposed to defining it at the connection level, do you agree?

I guess I could see both a default to use for all pig tasks (But I think this should really be set at the cluster level) and a task level value.
In this case, we could add the env param in the operator to be passed to the hook at init time.
